column19: Clearly I didn't understand the game or I'm not smart enough, but it was not clear to me exactly what the UI was trying to tell me. I could not see a way for a mandatory three word explanation was sufficient to eliminate all the objects. If the experiment was that it wasn't possible to win, then fair enough, but the fact that the game didn't have levels to progress one's skill and thus cement understanding means it felt like a pointless enterprise.
Difficulty pressing start to begin the game - had to refresh the window
One of the levels at the end didn't load and so I was just clicking random buttons until the 8 minutes was up
At the start. There seemed to be a glitch.

I wasn't aware of any bugs in the app but in the beginning it was a bit difficult to actually understand what to do. I started getting the hang of it as my remaining moves became less. I would enjoy doing a similar survey again. Thanks for the nice survey.

The only words that were applicable were blue and diamond which weren't three words. I figured this out quickly so was just trying to pass the 8 minutes as I knew I wouldn't be able to complete it.
